Set Up Routing for Messaging Channels in Service Cloud

Use Omni-Channel to route customer inquiries sent over Facebook Messenger, WhatsApp, Apple Messages, or SMS to a queue, bot, or qualified support agent.

Available in: Lightning Experience. This article applies to Standard and enhanced WhatsApp, standard and enhanced Facebook Messenger, standard and enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel.

When you configure routing for your enhanced Messaging channels, you can choose between using status-based and tab-based capacity.

 Omni-Channel Settings and Service Channels pages in Setup are used to configure capacity settings. Status-based capacity is in beta for enhanced Messaging channels and Messaging for In-App and Web.

Route customer messages sent over Facebook Messenger, WhatsApp, Apple Messages, or SMS to the right agent, queue, or bot using an Omni-Channel flow. Alternatively, use queue-based routing for simple scenarios.

 Route Service Cloud Messaging Sessions with Omni-Channel Flows

title: Setting Up Routing for Messaging Channels in Service Cloud
